        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} has a history notable for ongoing attention problems reported by both home and school, especially distractibility and difficulty sustaining concentration on age-appropriate tasks [SNOMED:F90.0]. Family members describe emotional impulsivity and emotionally reactive behavior during periods of frustration [SNOMED:F90.0]. There is also concern for executive-function difficulty, including poor organization and incomplete school assignments despite adequate effort [SNOMED:F90.0].\n\nShe has not had prior psychiatric hospitalization. No substance use is reported, which is consistent with her age. Sleep, appetite, and growth are being monitored because treatment for attention disorders may require follow-up of weight, height, pulse, and blood pressure as part of routine clinical care. She attends regular school classes and has supportive parents who are seeking evaluation because symptoms are interfering with academic progress and family routines."
          }
        ]
      }
